{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place spring onions\/shallots, garlic, Kaffir lime leaves, lemongrass, oil, ginger, palm sugar, coriander roots and stalks, chilli and turmeric into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>6 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and sauté <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add coconut milk, water and stock paste. Place Varoma into position and weigh mussels into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Carefully stir mussels to ensure even cooking, secure Varoma lid and steam for a further <nobr>7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Divide mussels between serving bowls and discard any that have not opened during cooking.","Add fish sauce and lime juice to mixing bowl and mix <nobr>6 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Pour broth over mussels and garnish with reserved fresh coriander leaves and sliced chillies to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["3 spring onions\/shallots, cut into halves","2 garlic cloves","2 fresh Kaffir lime leaves","1 stalk lemongrass, cut into thirds","20 g sesame oil","5 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","1 cube palm sugar (1-2 cm)","10 sprigs fresh coriander, roots and stalks for broth, leaves reserved for garnishing","1 fresh long red chilli, deseeded if preferred, plus extra, thinly sliced for garnishing","¾ tsp ground turmeric","400 g coconut milk","500 g water","1 - 2 tsp Chicken stock paste, to taste (see Tips)","1000 g fresh mussels, scrubbed and debearded","1 tsp fish sauce","20 g lime juice (approx. 1 lime)"]}],"id":"r249783","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-g1XoUUO-USQ\/XZQuon9cihI\/AAAAAAAAcVc\/MwEveJQ5S78jMvk5KLMIcDh-o2zmKDM_wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_3hZR67MBHSXF60Q8.png","title":"Mussels in turmeric and ginger broth","publishedAt":"2018-07-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11 g","fat":"24.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11.5 g","calories":"1313.2 kJ \/ 312.6 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving bowls","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the ground turmeric with a 1-2 cm piece fresh, peeled turmeric, if desired.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or the <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Chicken stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","20m","4 portions"]}